{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-tsx","path":"/tutorials/github-fork-sync","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1>Forks on GitHub</h1>\n<p>When you intent to contribute to a project, which is not owned by you or no one has given you write access to the repository, you’d usually do this via forks.\nBasically forking a repository means that you’re copying the repository to your account so that you can make changes to it.\nAfter the changes are done you may create a PR (pull request) against the original repository.</p>\n<h2>Forking a public repository</h2>\n<p>In order to create a fork you can navigate to this repository and hit the fork button:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/db461819c89056b6ca793baaaf1051fe/22475/fork-button-github.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.16216216216216%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"GitHub fork button\"\n        title=\"GitHub fork button\"\n        src=\"/static/db461819c89056b6ca793baaaf1051fe/fcda8/fork-button-github.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/db461819c89056b6ca793baaaf1051fe/12f09/fork-button-github.png 148w,\n/static/db461819c89056b6ca793baaaf1051fe/e4a3f/fork-button-github.png 295w,\n/static/db461819c89056b6ca793baaaf1051fe/fcda8/fork-button-github.png 590w,\n/static/db461819c89056b6ca793baaaf1051fe/efc66/fork-button-github.png 885w,\n/static/db461819c89056b6ca793baaaf1051fe/22475/fork-button-github.png 1039w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>When clicking the fork button you should see a similar dialog, where you can choose where to copy the repository.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 447px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/c80a1dca135e85cbf0e0742c67c9aefb/a2d48/fork-dialog-github.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 82.43243243243244%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"GitHub fork button\"\n        title=\"GitHub fork button\"\n        src=\"/static/c80a1dca135e85cbf0e0742c67c9aefb/a2d48/fork-dialog-github.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/c80a1dca135e85cbf0e0742c67c9aefb/12f09/fork-dialog-github.png 148w,\n/static/c80a1dca135e85cbf0e0742c67c9aefb/e4a3f/fork-dialog-github.png 295w,\n/static/c80a1dca135e85cbf0e0742c67c9aefb/a2d48/fork-dialog-github.png 447w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 447px) 100vw, 447px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Once this has been done you can clone the forked repository, change it according to your needs and also provide a PR for the original repository.</p>\n<h1>Sync fork with upstream</h1>\n<p>Of course your fork belongs to you and therefore will remain unchanged while the original repository evolves.\nTo catch up with the changes you might want to sync your own repository with the original repository`s master branch.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/31361031658aae3dae7e68a9692b98f0/3a5d5/branch-behind-forked-repo.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 15.54054054054054%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAADCAIAAAAcOLh5AAAACXBIWXMAAA7EAAAOxAGVKw4bAAAAhElEQVQI1zWOOw7DMAxDff/jdeyWoUljF3GA2PpacoUiJd5CQiKYPmd7HbRWAlaWG2IJRIeoqdr0aeY/OwAJiAC5dUxMyETKjICt9d4BAEWEWcYwIo6WR3ku5+pjRhL/5h64zzRDqgHXeu255XK9dwEwj9MRKzrgUrftyHkvtZ7RPf/6AjdCrb+loWSsAAAAAElFTkSuQmCC'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Branch behind forked repo\"\n        title=\"Branch behind forked repo\"\n        src=\"/static/31361031658aae3dae7e68a9692b98f0/fcda8/branch-behind-forked-repo.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/31361031658aae3dae7e68a9692b98f0/12f09/branch-behind-forked-repo.png 148w,\n/static/31361031658aae3dae7e68a9692b98f0/e4a3f/branch-behind-forked-repo.png 295w,\n/static/31361031658aae3dae7e68a9692b98f0/fcda8/branch-behind-forked-repo.png 590w,\n/static/31361031658aae3dae7e68a9692b98f0/efc66/branch-behind-forked-repo.png 885w,\n/static/31361031658aae3dae7e68a9692b98f0/c83ae/branch-behind-forked-repo.png 1180w,\n/static/31361031658aae3dae7e68a9692b98f0/3a5d5/branch-behind-forked-repo.png 1807w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Add the original repository as remote</h2>\n<p>See existing remotes:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> remote -v</code></pre></div>\n<p>This command usually shows the <code class=\"language-text\">origin</code> remote, which points to your forked repository.</p>\n<p>To also get (read) access to the original repository an upstream remote can be added:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> remote <span class=\"token function\">add</span> upstream https://github.com/ORIGINAL_OWNER/ORIGINAL_REPOSITORY.git\n\ne.g.\n\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> remote <span class=\"token function\">add</span> upstream git@github.com:gradle/gradle.git</code></pre></div>\n<p>When <code class=\"language-text\">git remote -v</code> is invoked once again there should be an <code class=\"language-text\">upstream</code> remote besides the existing <code class=\"language-text\">origin</code> remote.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/708af27e2697134a0aeeaa840f610bfe/f058b/git-remote-v.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 15.54054054054054%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"git remote -v command\"\n        title=\"git remote -v command\"\n        src=\"/static/708af27e2697134a0aeeaa840f610bfe/fcda8/git-remote-v.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/708af27e2697134a0aeeaa840f610bfe/12f09/git-remote-v.png 148w,\n/static/708af27e2697134a0aeeaa840f610bfe/e4a3f/git-remote-v.png 295w,\n/static/708af27e2697134a0aeeaa840f610bfe/fcda8/git-remote-v.png 590w,\n/static/708af27e2697134a0aeeaa840f610bfe/f058b/git-remote-v.png 630w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Sync fork with the upstream master</h2>\n<p>To get the latest changes from the upstream remote you checkout the master branch (usually left untouched, because your changes are in feature or bugfix branches) and then fetch + merge the changes from the upstream master branch.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\"><span class=\"token function\">git</span> checkout master\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> fetch upstream\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> merge upstream/master\n<span class=\"token function\">git</span> push origin master</code></pre></div>\n<p>After merging the changes from the upstream remote your own master branch is even with the upstream.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/569193a75615ba0415009c105cf058d1/776d3/branch-even-forked-repo.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 14.18918918918919%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAADCAIAAAAcOLh5AAAACXBIWXMAAA7EAAAOxAGVKw4bAAAAfElEQVQI1z2NyQ7DIAxE+f+v6zG3Xqq0QBKhFIMXAp1EbZ/Gkj3e3GOt88bEKmp/sZyltUMRrY8+kEDwqdZyiqlUJyImDHImokKlMMMTLImqij3f8RYmDLQLa+3oX9wAZrKs+8tnH8gHdNFv11tmnbc4xXsAcUkp4eD48QE+4a2vLRf7ZAAAAABJRU5ErkJggg=='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Branch even with forked repo\"\n        title=\"Branch even with forked repo\"\n        src=\"/static/569193a75615ba0415009c105cf058d1/fcda8/branch-even-forked-repo.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/569193a75615ba0415009c105cf058d1/12f09/branch-even-forked-repo.png 148w,\n/static/569193a75615ba0415009c105cf058d1/e4a3f/branch-even-forked-repo.png 295w,\n/static/569193a75615ba0415009c105cf058d1/fcda8/branch-even-forked-repo.png 590w,\n/static/569193a75615ba0415009c105cf058d1/efc66/branch-even-forked-repo.png 885w,\n/static/569193a75615ba0415009c105cf058d1/c83ae/branch-even-forked-repo.png 1180w,\n/static/569193a75615ba0415009c105cf058d1/776d3/branch-even-forked-repo.png 1814w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>","timeToRead":2,"frontmatter":{"date":"November 20, 2020","title":"GitHub forking and syncing","author":"Simon Scholz"}}},"pageContext":{}},"staticQueryHashes":["2006812849","2917690675"]}